JDK, JRE, JVM – 50 TRICKY INTERVIEW QUESTIONS WITH WHY + TECHNICAL EXAMPLES

1. What is JVM?
Answer: JVM (Java Virtual Machine) executes Java bytecode.
Why: It provides platform independence.
Example: .class file runs on any OS with JVM.

2. What is JRE?
Answer: JRE = JVM + libraries.
Why: Required to run Java programs.
Example: Running Java app without compiler.

3. What is JDK?
Answer: JDK = JRE + Development tools.
Why: Needed to develop Java programs.
Example: javac compiles code.

4. Can we run Java without JDK?
Answer: Yes (using JRE).
Why: Execution needs JVM, not compiler.

5. Can we compile Java without JRE?
Answer: No.
Why: JDK already includes JRE.

6. What is bytecode?
Answer: Intermediate code (.class file).
Why: Platform-independent execution.
Example: javac Test.java → Test.class

7. Who converts bytecode to machine code?
Answer: JVM.
Why: Uses interpreter/JIT compiler.

8. What is JIT compiler?
Answer: Converts bytecode to native code at runtime.
Why: Improves performance.
Example: Frequently used methods optimized.

9. Is JVM platform dependent?
Answer: Yes.
Why: Each OS has its own JVM implementation.

10. Is Java platform independent?
Answer: Yes.
Why: Bytecode runs on any JVM.

11. Can we install JRE without JDK?
Answer: Yes.
Why: Only runtime needed.

12. Can we install JDK without JRE?
Answer: No.
Why: JDK includes JRE.

13. What is classloader?
Answer: Loads classes into memory.
Why: Dynamic loading.
Example: Loads Test.class at runtime.

14. Types of classloaders?
Answer: Bootstrap, Extension, Application.
Why: Organized loading hierarchy.

15. What is Heap memory?
Answer: Object storage area.
Why: Dynamic memory allocation.
Example: new Object() stored here.

16. What is Stack memory?
Answer: Stores method calls.
Why: Faster access.
Example: method execution frames.

17. What is Method Area?
Answer: Stores class metadata.
Why: Needed for execution.

18. What is Garbage Collection?
Answer: Automatic memory cleanup.
Why: Removes unused objects.
Example: object = null → eligible for GC.

19. Can we force GC?
Answer: No (only request).
Why: JVM decides execution.

20. What is Runtime class?
Answer: Provides runtime info.
Why: Interaction with JVM.

21. What is JNI?
Answer: Java Native Interface.
Why: Connects Java with C/C++.

22. What is interpreter in JVM?
Answer: Executes bytecode line by line.
Why: Simplicity but slower.

23. Difference between JIT and Interpreter?
Answer: JIT compiles, interpreter executes line-by-line.
Why: JIT is faster.

24. Can JVM run non-Java code?
Answer: Yes (via bytecode).
Why: Any language compiled to bytecode works.

25. Example of non-Java JVM language?
Answer: Kotlin, Scala.
Why: They compile to bytecode.

26. What is execution engine?
Answer: Part of JVM.
Why: Executes bytecode.

27. What is verification phase?
Answer: Checks bytecode safety.
Why: Security.

28. What is linking phase?
Answer: Prepares classes.
Why: Memory allocation.

29. What is initialization phase?
Answer: Assigns values.
Why: Final step before execution.

30. What is classpath?
Answer: Path to locate classes.
Why: JVM needs it.

31. Can we run Java program without main?
Answer: Yes (static block in older versions).
Why: Class loading triggers execution.

32. What is bootstrap classloader?
Answer: Loads core Java classes.
Why: Foundational classes.

33. What is extension classloader?
Answer: Loads extension libraries.

34. What is application classloader?
Answer: Loads user classes.

35. What is JVM architecture?
Answer: Classloader + Memory + Execution Engine.

36. Why Java is secure?
Answer: Bytecode verification.
Why: Prevents unsafe code.

37. What is OutOfMemoryError?
Answer: Heap memory full.
Why: No space for objects.

38. What is StackOverflowError?
Answer: Stack full.
Why: Infinite recursion.

39. Can JVM be written in Java?
Answer: No (needs native support).

40. What is HotSpot JVM?
Answer: Optimized JVM.
Why: Better performance.

41. What is AOT compilation?
Answer: Compile before execution.
Why: Faster startup.

42. What is dynamic class loading?
Answer: Load classes at runtime.

43. What is memory leak in Java?
Answer: Unused objects not GC’d.

44. What is permgen/metaspace?
Answer: Class metadata storage.

45. What happens when JVM starts?
Answer: Loads classes → executes main.

46. Can multiple JVM run?
Answer: Yes.

47. What is thread stack?
Answer: Each thread has its own stack.

48. What is daemon thread?
Answer: Background thread.

49. What is JVM shutdown?
Answer: Ends execution.

50. Why JVM is important?
Answer: Platform independence + memory management.

